description: Creates a staging distribution using the configuration of the provided primary distribution. A staging distribution is a copy of an existing distribution (called the primary distribution) that you can use in a continuous deployment workflow. After you create a staging distribution, you can use UpdateDistribution to modify the staging distribution's configuration. Then you can use CreateContinuousDeploymentPolicy to incrementally move traffic to the staging distribution. This API operation requires the following IAM permissions:

parameters.name: PrimaryDistributionId
parameters.description: The identifier of the primary distribution whose configuration you are copying. To get a distribution ID, use ListDistributions.

parameters.name: CallerReference
parameters.description: A value that uniquely identifies a request to create a resource. This helps to prevent CloudFront from creating a duplicate resource if you accidentally resubmit an identical request.

parameters.name: Enabled
parameters.description: A Boolean flag to specify the state of the staging distribution when it's created. When you set this value to True, the staging distribution is enabled. When you set this value to False, the staging distribution is disabled. If you omit this field, the default value is True.

nested_items.name: Distribution
nested_items.description: A distribution tells CloudFront where you want content to be delivered from, and the details about how to track and manage content delivery.

nested_items.name: Id
nested_items.description: The distribution's identifier. For example: E1U5RQF7T870K0.

nested_items.name: ARN
nested_items.description: The distribution's Amazon Resource Name (ARN).

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: The distribution's status. When the status is Deployed, the distribution's information is fully propagated to all CloudFront edge locations.

nested_items.name: LastModifiedTime
nested_items.description: The date and time when the distribution was last modified.

nested_items.name: InProgressInvalidationBatches
nested_items.description: The number of invalidation batches currently in progress.

nested_items.name: DomainName
nested_items.description: The distribution's CloudFront domain name. For example: d111111abcdef8.cloudfront.net.

nested_items.name: ActiveTrustedSigners
nested_items.description: This field contains a list of Amazon Web Services account IDs and the active CloudFront key pairs in each account that CloudFront can use to verify the signatures of signed URLs or signed cookies.

nested_items.name: Enabled
nested_items.description: This field is true if any of the Amazon Web Services accounts in the list are configured as trusted signers. If not, this field is false.

nested_items.name: Quantity
nested_items.description: The number of Amazon Web Services accounts in the list.

nested_items.name: Items
nested_items.description: A list of Amazon Web Services accounts and the identifiers of active CloudFront key pairs in each account that CloudFront can use to verify the signatures of signed URLs and signed cookies.

nested_items.name: AwsAccountNumber
nested_items.description: An Amazon Web Services account number that contains active CloudFront key pairs that CloudFront can use to verify the signatures of signed URLs and signed cookies. If the Amazon Web Services account that owns the key pairs is the same account that owns the CloudFront distribution, the value of this field is self.

nested_items.name: KeyPairIds
nested_items.description: A list of CloudFront key pair identifiers.

nested_items.name: Quantity
nested_items.description: The number of key pair identifiers in the list.

nested_items.name: Items
nested_items.description: A list of CloudFront key pair identifiers.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: ActiveTrustedKeyGroups
nested_items.description: This field contains a list of key groups and the public keys in each key group that CloudFront can use to verify the signatures of signed URLs or signed cookies.

nested_items.name: Enabled
nested_items.description: This field is true if any of the key groups have public keys that CloudFront can use to verify the signatures of signed URLs and signed cookies. If not, this field is false.

nested_items.name: Quantity
nested_items.description: The number of key groups in the list.

nested_items.name: Items
nested_items.description: A list of key groups, including the identifiers of the public keys in each key group that CloudFront can use to verify the signatures of signed URLs and signed cookies.

nested_items.name: KeyGroupId
nested_items.description: The identifier of the key group that contains the public keys.

nested_items.name: KeyPairIds

nested_items.name: Quantity

nested_items.name: DistributionConfig
nested_items.description: The distribution's configuration.

nested_items.name: CallerReference
nested_items.description: A unique value (for example, a date-time stamp) that ensures that the request can't be replayed.

nested_items.name: Quantity
nested_items.description: The number of CNAME aliases, if any, that you want to associate with this distribution.

nested_items.name: Items
nested_items.description: A complex type that contains the CNAME aliases, if any, that you want to associate with this distribution.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: DefaultRootObject
nested_items.description: When a viewer requests the root URL for your distribution, the default root object is the object that you want CloudFront to request from your origin. For example, if your root URL is https://www.example.com, you can specify CloudFront to return the index.html file as the default root object. You can specify a default root object so that viewers see a specific file or object, instead of another object in your distribution (for example, https://www.example.com/product-description.html). A default root object avoids exposing the contents of your distribution.

nested_items.name: Quantity
nested_items.description: The number of origins for this distribution.

nested_items.name: Items
nested_items.description: A list of origins.
Use S3OriginConfig to specify an Amazon S3 bucket that is not configured with static website hosting.
Use VpcOriginConfig to specify a VPC origin.
Use CustomOriginConfig to specify all other kinds of origins, including:
An Amazon S3 bucket that is configured with static website hosting.
An Elastic Load Balancing load balancer.
An Elemental MediaPackage endpoint.
An Elemental MediaStore container.
Any other HTTP server, running on an Amazon EC2 instance or any other kind of host.

nested_items.description: A complex type that contains information about origin groups for this distribution.

nested_items.name: Quantity
nested_items.description: The number of origin groups.

nested_items.name: Items

nested_items.description: A complex type that contains information about the failover criteria for an origin group.

nested_items.description: A complex type that describes the default cache behavior if you don't specify a CacheBehavior element or if files don't match any of the values of PathPattern in CacheBehavior elements. You must create exactly one default cache behavior.

nested_items.name: TargetOriginId
nested_items.description: The value of ID for the origin that you want CloudFront to route requests to when they use the default cache behavior.

nested_items.name: TrustedSigners
nested_items.description: A list of Amazon Web Services account IDs whose public keys CloudFront can use to validate signed URLs or signed cookies.

nested_items.name: Enabled
nested_items.description: This field is true if any of the Amazon Web Services accounts in the list are configured as trusted signers. If not, this field is false.

nested_items.name: Quantity

nested_items.name: Items
nested_items.description: A list of Amazon Web Services account identifiers.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: Enabled

nested_items.name: Quantity

nested_items.name: Items

nested_items.name: ViewerProtocolPolicy
nested_items.description: The protocol that viewers can use to access the files in the origin specified by TargetOriginId when a request matches the path pattern in PathPattern. You can specify the following options:
allow-all: Viewers can use HTTP or HTTPS.

redirect-to-https: If a viewer submits an HTTP request, CloudFront returns an HTTP status code of 301 (Moved Permanently) to the viewer along with the HTTPS URL. The viewer then resubmits the request using the new URL.
https-only: If a viewer sends an HTTP request, CloudFront returns an HTTP status code of 403 (Forbidden).

nested_items.name: AllowedMethods
nested_items.description: A complex type that controls which HTTP methods CloudFront processes and forwards to your Amazon S3 bucket or your custom origin. There are three choices:
CloudFront forwards only GET and HEAD requests.
CloudFront forwards only GET, HEAD, and OPTIONS requests.
CloudFront forwards GET, HEAD, OPTIONS, PUT, PATCH, POST, and DELETE requests.

nested_items.name: SmoothStreaming
nested_items.description: Indicates whether you want to distribute media files in the Microsoft Smooth Streaming format using the origin that is associated with this cache behavior. If so, specify true; if not, specify false. If you specify true for SmoothStreaming, you can still distribute other content using this cache behavior if the content matches the value of PathPattern.

nested_items.name: Compress
nested_items.description: Whether you want CloudFront to automatically compress certain files for this cache behavior. If so, specify true; if not, specify false. For more information, see Serving Compressed Files in the Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide.

nested_items.name: LambdaFunctionAssociations
nested_items.description: A complex type that contains zero or more Lambda@Edge function associations for a cache behavior.

nested_items.name: Quantity
nested_items.description: The number of Lambda@Edge function associations for this cache behavior.

nested_items.name: Items
nested_items.description: Optional: A complex type that contains LambdaFunctionAssociation items for this cache behavior. If Quantity is 0, you can omit Items.

nested_items.name: LambdaFunctionARN
nested_items.description: The ARN of the Lambda@Edge function. You must specify the ARN of a function version; you can't specify an alias or $LATEST.

nested_items.name: EventType
nested_items.description: Specifies the event type that triggers a Lambda@Edge function invocation. You can specify the following values:
viewer-request: The function executes when CloudFront receives a request from a viewer and before it checks to see whether the requested object is in the edge cache.
origin-request: The function executes only when CloudFront sends a request to your origin. When the requested object is in the edge cache, the function doesn't execute.

origin-response: The function executes after CloudFront receives a response from the origin and before it caches the object in the response. When the requested object is in the edge cache, the function doesn't execute.

viewer-response: The function executes before CloudFront returns the requested object to the viewer. The function executes regardless of whether the object was already in the edge cache. If the origin returns an HTTP status code other than HTTP 200 (OK), the function doesn't execute.

nested_items.name: IncludeBody
nested_items.description: A flag that allows a Lambda@Edge function to have read access to the body content. For more information, see Accessing the Request Body by Choosing the Include Body Option in the Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide.

nested_items.name: FunctionAssociations
nested_items.description: A list of CloudFront functions that are associated with this cache behavior. Your functions must be published to the LIVE stage to associate them with a cache behavior.

nested_items.name: Quantity
nested_items.description: The number of CloudFront functions in the list.

nested_items.name: Items
nested_items.description: The CloudFront functions that are associated with a cache behavior in a CloudFront distribution. Your functions must be published to the LIVE stage to associate them with a cache behavior.

nested_items.name: FunctionARN
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the function.

nested_items.name: EventType
nested_items.description: The event type of the function, either viewer-request or viewer-response. You cannot use origin-facing event types ( origin-request and origin-response) with a CloudFront function.

nested_items.name: FieldLevelEncryptionId
nested_items.description: The value of ID for the field-level encryption configuration that you want CloudFront to use for encrypting specific fields of data for the default cache behavior.

nested_items.name: RealtimeLogConfigArn

nested_items.name: CachePolicyId

nested_items.name: OriginRequestPolicyId

nested_items.description: A complex type that controls the following:
Whether CloudFront replaces HTTP status codes in the 4xx and 5xx range with custom error messages before returning the response to the viewer.
How long CloudFront caches HTTP status codes in the 4xx and 5xx range.

nested_items.name: Comment
nested_items.description: A comment to describe the distribution. The comment cannot be longer than 128 characters.

nested_items.name: Enabled
nested_items.description: Specifies whether you want CloudFront to save access logs to an Amazon S3 bucket. If you don't want to enable logging when you create a distribution or if you want to disable logging for an existing distribution, specify false for Enabled, and specify empty Bucket and Prefix elements. If you specify false for Enabled but you specify values for Bucket and prefix, the values are automatically deleted.

nested_items.name: IncludeCookies
nested_items.description: Specifies whether you want CloudFront to include cookies in access logs, specify true for IncludeCookies. If you choose to include cookies in logs, CloudFront logs all cookies regardless of how you configure the cache behaviors for this distribution. If you don't want to include cookies when you create a distribution or if you want to disable include cookies for an existing distribution, specify false for IncludeCookies.

nested_items.name: Bucket
nested_items.description: The Amazon S3 bucket to store the access logs in, for example, amzn-s3-demo-bucket.s3.amazonaws.com.

nested_items.name: Prefix
nested_items.description: An optional string that you want CloudFront to prefix to the access log filenames for this distribution, for example, myprefix/. If you want to enable logging, but you don't want to specify a prefix, you still must include an empty Prefix element in the Logging element.

nested_items.name: PriceClass
nested_items.description: The price class that corresponds with the maximum price that you want to pay for CloudFront service. If you specify PriceClass_All, CloudFront responds to requests for your objects from all CloudFront edge locations.

nested_items.name: Enabled
nested_items.description: From this field, you can enable or disable the selected distribution.

nested_items.description: A complex type that determines the distribution's SSL/TLS configuration for communicating with viewers.

nested_items.name: CloudFrontDefaultCertificate
nested_items.description: If the distribution uses the CloudFront domain name such as d111111abcdef8.cloudfront.net, set this field to true.

nested_items.type: specify a value for one, not both
nested_items.description: ACMCertificateArn or IAMCertificateId (specify a value for one, not both)
MinimumProtocolVersion.
SSLSupportMethod.

nested_items.name: IAMCertificateId
nested_items.description: If the distribution uses Aliases (alternate domain names or CNAMEs) and the SSL/TLS certificate is stored in Identity and Access Management (IAM), provide the ID of the IAM certificate.

nested_items.name: ACMCertificateArn
nested_items.description: If the distribution uses Aliases (alternate domain names or CNAMEs) and the SSL/TLS certificate is stored in Certificate Manager (ACM), provide the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the ACM certificate. CloudFront only supports ACM certificates in the US East (N. Virginia) Region ( us-east-1).

nested_items.name: SSLSupportMethod
nested_items.description: If the distribution uses Aliases (alternate domain names or CNAMEs), specify which viewers the distribution accepts HTTPS connections from.
sni-only --- The distribution accepts HTTPS connections from only viewers that support server name indication (SNI). This is recommended. Most browsers and clients support SNI.
vip --- The distribution accepts HTTPS connections from all viewers including those that don't support SNI. This is not recommended, and results in additional monthly charges from CloudFront.

static-ip - Do not specify this value unless your distribution has been enabled for this feature by the CloudFront team. If you have a use case that requires static IP addresses for a distribution, contact CloudFront through the Amazon Web Services Support Center.

nested_items.name: MinimumProtocolVersion
nested_items.description: If the distribution uses Aliases (alternate domain names or CNAMEs), specify the security policy that you want CloudFront to use for HTTPS connections with viewers. The security policy determines two settings:
The minimum SSL/TLS protocol that CloudFront can use to communicate with viewers.
The ciphers that CloudFront can use to encrypt the content that it returns to viewers.

nested_items.name: Restrictions
nested_items.description: A complex type that identifies ways in which you want to restrict distribution of your content.

nested_items.name: GeoRestriction
nested_items.description: A complex type that controls the countries in which your content is distributed. CloudFront determines the location of your users using MaxMind GeoIP databases.

nested_items.name: RestrictionType
nested_items.description: The method that you want to use to restrict distribution of your content by country:
none: No geo restriction is enabled, meaning access to content is not restricted by client geo location.
blacklist: The Location elements specify the countries in which you don't want CloudFront to distribute your content.
whitelist: The Location elements specify the countries in which you want CloudFront to distribute your content.

nested_items.name: Quantity
nested_items.description: When geo restriction is enabled, this is the number of countries in your whitelist or blacklist. Otherwise, when it is not enabled, Quantity is 0, and you can omit Items.

nested_items.name: Items
nested_items.description: A complex type that contains a Location element for each country in which you want CloudFront either to distribute your content ( whitelist) or not distribute your content ( blacklist).
(string) ---

nested_items.name: WebACLId
nested_items.description: A unique identifier that specifies the WAF web ACL, if any, to associate with this distribution. To specify a web ACL created using the latest version of WAF, use the ACL ARN, for example arn:aws:wafv2:us-east-1:123456789012:global/webacl/ExampleWebACL/a1b2c3d4-5678-90ab-cdef-EXAMPLE11111. To specify a web ACL created using WAF Classic, use the ACL ID, for example a1b2c3d4-5678-90ab-cdef-EXAMPLE11111.

nested_items.name: HttpVersion
nested_items.description: (Optional) Specify the HTTP version(s) that you want viewers to use to communicate with CloudFront. The default value for new web distributions is http2. Viewers that don't support HTTP/2 automatically use an earlier HTTP version.

nested_items.name: IsIPV6Enabled
nested_items.description: If you want CloudFront to respond to IPv6 DNS requests with an IPv6 address for your distribution, specify true. If you specify false, CloudFront responds to IPv6 DNS requests with the DNS response code NOERROR and with no IP addresses. This allows viewers to submit a second request, for an IPv4 address for your distribution.
You enable IPv6 for the distribution.
You're using alternate domain names in the URLs for your objects.

nested_items.name: ContinuousDeploymentPolicyId
nested_items.description: The identifier of a continuous deployment policy. For more information, see CreateContinuousDeploymentPolicy.

nested_items.name: Staging
nested_items.description: A Boolean that indicates whether this is a staging distribution. When this value is true, this is a staging distribution. When this value is false, this is not a staging distribution.

nested_items.name: AnycastIpListId
nested_items.description: ID of the Anycast static IP list that is associated with the distribution.

nested_items.name: TenantConfig
nested_items.description: A distribution tenant configuration.

nested_items.name: ParameterDefinitions
nested_items.description: The parameters that you specify for a distribution tenant.

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: The name of the parameter.

nested_items.name: Definition
nested_items.description: The value that you assigned to the parameter.

nested_items.name: StringSchema
nested_items.description: An object that contains information about the string schema.

nested_items.name: Comment
nested_items.description: A comment to describe the parameter.

nested_items.name: DefaultValue
nested_items.description: The default value of the parameter.

nested_items.name: Required
nested_items.description: Whether the defined parameter is required.

nested_items.name: ConnectionMode
nested_items.description: The connection mode to filter distributions by.

nested_items.name: AliasICPRecordals
nested_items.description: Amazon Web Services services in China customers must file for an Internet Content Provider (ICP) recordal if they want to serve content publicly on an alternate domain name, also known as a CNAME, that they've added to CloudFront. AliasICPRecordal provides the ICP recordal status for CNAMEs associated with distributions.

nested_items.name: CNAME
nested_items.description: A domain name associated with a distribution.

nested_items.name: ICPRecordalStatus
nested_items.description: The Internet Content Provider (ICP) recordal status for a CNAME. The ICPRecordalStatus is set to APPROVED for all CNAMEs (aliases) in Amazon Web Services Regions outside of China.

nested_items.name: Location
nested_items.description: The URL of the staging distribution.

nested_items.name: ETag
nested_items.description: The version identifier for the current version of the staging distribution.
